# Analysing weak points for vip_at_risk_segment
df_vip_at_risk_segment = pd.read_csv('vip_at_risk_segment.csv')

# Rating columns (excluding percentage columns)
rating_cols = ['seat_comfort', 'leg_room_service', 'food_and_drink',
               'inflight_entertainment', 'inflight_wifi_service', 'cleanliness',
               'on_board_service', 'inflight_service', 'checkin_service',
               'online_boarding', 'ease_of_online_booking', 'baggage_handling',
               'gate_location', 'departure_arrival_time_convenience']

# Calculate average
average_ratings = df_vip_at_risk_segment[rating_cols].mean().sort_values()

# Create horizontal bar chart
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 8))
bars = plt.barh(range(len(average_ratings)), average_ratings, color='#4ECDC4', alpha=0.8)

plt.title('VIP at Risk Segment: Average Ratings (Sorted)', fontsize=14, fontweight='bold')
plt.xlabel('Average Rating Score', fontsize=12)
plt.ylabel('Service Attributes', fontsize=12)
plt.yticks(range(len(average_ratings)), average_ratings.index)
plt.xlim(0, 5.5)
plt.grid(True, alpha=0.3, axis='x')

# Add value labels
for i, bar in enumerate(bars):
    width = bar.get_width()
    plt.text(width + 0.05, bar.get_y() + bar.get_height()/2,
             f'{width:.2f}', va='center')

plt.tight_layout()
plt.savefig('vip_at_risk_avg_ratings.png', dpi=300, bbox_inches='tight')
plt.show()
print("Graph saved as: vip_at_risk_avg_ratings.png")

# Combined customer segment rating

# Load all segments
segments = {
    'VIP_at_risk_segment': pd.read_csv('vip_at_risk_segment.csv'),
    'Budget_explorers_segment': pd.read_csv('budget_explorers_segment.csv'),
    'Comfort_seekers_segment': pd.read_csv('comfort_seekers_segment.csv'),
    'Churn_prone_business_segment': pd.read_csv('churn_prone_business_segment.csv'),
    'Disloyal_high_value_segment': pd.read_csv('disloyal_high_value_segment.csv')
}

# Calculate average ratings for each segment
segment_averages = {}
for name, df_segment in segments.items():
    segment_averages[name] = df_segment[rating_cols].mean()

# Create DataFrame
avg_df = pd.DataFrame(segment_averages).T

# Create clustered bar chart
plt.figure(figsize=(18, 10))
x = np.arange(len(rating_cols))
width = 0.16
colors = ['#4ECDC4', '#FFA07A', '#9370DB', '#20B2AA', '#FF6347']

for i, (segment, color) in enumerate(zip(avg_df.index, colors)):
    offset = (i - 2) * width  # Center the bars
    plt.bar(x + offset, avg_df.loc[segment], width, label=segment, 
            color=color, alpha=0.8)

plt.title('Average Ratings Comparison Across All Segments', fontsize=16, fontweight='bold')
plt.ylabel('Average Rating Score', fontsize=14)
plt.xlabel('Service Attributes', fontsize=14)
plt.xticks(x, rating_cols, rotation=45, ha='right')
plt.legend()
plt.grid(True, alpha=0.3, axis='y')
plt.ylim(0, 5.5)

plt.tight_layout()
plt.savefig('all_segments_ratings_comparison.png', dpi=300, bbox_inches='tight')
plt.show()
print("Graph saved as: all_segments_ratings_comparison.png")

Graph saved as: all_segments_ratings_comparison.png

# Satisfaction Rate

# Load all segments
segments = {
    'VIP_at_risk': pd.read_csv('vip_at_risk_segment.csv'),
    'Budget_explorers': pd.read_csv('budget_explorers_segment.csv'),
    'Comfort_seekers': pd.read_csv('comfort_seekers_segment.csv'),
    'Churn_prone_business': pd.read_csv('churn_prone_business_segment.csv'),
    'Disloyal_high_value': pd.read_csv('disloyal_high_value_segment.csv')
}

print("Satisfaction Rates by Segment:")
print("=" * 40)

for segment_name, df_segment in segments.items():
    if len(df_segment) > 0:
        if 'satisfaction_bool' in df_segment.columns:
            satisfaction_rate = (df_segment['satisfaction_bool'].sum() / len(df_segment)) * 100
        elif 'satisfaction' in df_segment.columns:
            satisfied_count = df_segment['satisfaction'].apply(lambda x: 1 if 'satisfied' in str(x).lower() else 0).sum()
            satisfaction_rate = (satisfied_count / len(df_segment)) * 100
        else:
            satisfaction_rate = 'N/A'
        
        print(f"{segment_name:<25}: {satisfaction_rate if satisfaction_rate == 'N/A' else f'{satisfaction_rate:.2f}%'}")
    else:
        print(f"{segment_name:<25}: No data available")

# Flight Distance for each segment

# Calculate flight distance statistics for each segment
distance_stats = {}

for segment_name, df_segment in segments.items():
    if 'flight_distance' in df_segment.columns and len(df_segment) > 0:
        distance_stats[segment_name] = {
            'min': df_segment['flight_distance'].min(),
            'average': df_segment['flight_distance'].mean(),
            'max': df_segment['flight_distance'].max()
        }

# Create pivot DataFrame
distance_df = pd.DataFrame(distance_stats).T.round(2)

print("Flight Distance Statistics by Segment:")
print(distance_df)

# Create clustered bar chart
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 7))
x = np.arange(len(distance_df))
width = 0.25

plt.bar(x - width, distance_df['min'], width, label='Min', color='#FF6B6B', alpha=0.8)
plt.bar(x, distance_df['average'], width, label='Average', color='#4ECDC4', alpha=0.8)
plt.bar(x + width, distance_df['max'], width, label='Max', color='#45B7D1', alpha=0.8)

plt.title('Flight Distance Statistics by Segment', fontsize=14, fontweight='bold')
plt.ylabel('Flight Distance (miles)', fontsize=12)
plt.xlabel('Customer Segments', fontsize=12)
plt.xticks(x, distance_df.index, rotation=45, ha='right')
plt.legend()
plt.grid(True, alpha=0.3, axis='y')

plt.tight_layout()
plt.savefig('segment_flight_distance_stats.png', dpi=300, bbox_inches='tight')
plt.show()
print("Graph saved as: segment_flight_distance_stats.png")

# Top 3 Pain Points

# Find top 3 pain points (lowest average ratings) for each segment
top_pain_points = {}

for segment_name, df_segment in segments.items():
    if len(df_segment) > 0:
        # Calculate average ratings
        avg_ratings = df_segment[rating_cols].mean()
        # Get top 3 pain points (lowest ratings)
        pain_points = avg_ratings.nsmallest(3)
        top_pain_points[segment_name] = pain_points

# Create DataFrame
pain_df = pd.DataFrame(top_pain_points).round(2)

print("Top 3 Pain Points by Segment (Lowest Ratings):")
print(pain_df)

# Create heatmap
# Create heatmap with custom color gradient
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 8))
sns.heatmap(pain_df, annot=True, cmap='RdYlGn', center=3, 
            linewidths=1, linecolor='white', cbar_kws={'label': 'Rating Score'})
plt.title('Top 3 Pain Points by Customer Segment', fontsize=14, fontweight='bold')
plt.xlabel('Customer Segments', fontsize=12)
plt.ylabel('Service Attributes', fontsize=12)
plt.tight_layout()
plt.savefig('segment_pain_points_heatmap.png', dpi=300, bbox_inches='tight')
plt.show()
print("Graph saved as: segment_pain_points_heatmap.png")
